</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzakiwi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zakiwi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/4/02 5:09:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=796.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbies and Ports</span><hr size=1> When I am playing my ranger, if a guild porter or a friend isn't free to port me, I walk and take boats. Doesn't really seem like a big deal and doesn't take that long, plus it is fun to just run around the world exploring. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utehutibloodstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tehuti Bloodstorm</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/4/02 5:14:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=796.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.toddalan.com/~berglund/ikp_hao.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbies and Ports</span><hr size=1> My favorite was a level 8 necro twink that wanted to port to DL so he could buy some flayed skin armor.<br>
<br>
I told him he would die, but he was insistant.<br>
<br>
So, I ported him. Stayed grouped so I could watch his life bar drop, but he went LD about 2 minutes later.<br>
<br>
Never heard from him again. ^^ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uinkiewiz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Inkiewiz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/5/02 10:45:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=796.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbies and Ports</span><hr size=1> My first port (on my main at level 23), I felt like I was flying.  I felt like the wizzie was Superman tucking me under his arm.  Just so cool. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I can't fathom beggars.  Have some pride, sheesh!  I especially hate the alts masquerading as true newbies.  Mmm, you don't fool me, thanks.<br>
<br>
I think I probably got a lot of the gifts that I did because I never asked.  (And, well, maybe 'cause I was a half-naked female.  Didn't have pants till Oasis <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )  <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umorifen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Morifen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/5/02 10:06:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=796.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbies and Ports</span><hr size=1> Lol....at lvl 20 I still dont think I even had armor yet for a couple of my slots.   Got a Flowing black robe at about lvl 24-26, was soo friggin uber, i was so happy.   SLowed down my lvling around that time, and bought a staff of writhing a few month later for 500pp when they were still selling in the 500-1000pp range.  Same price as gatorscale sleeves and some other stuff.   I remember casting my gate to cazik shortly after i gained lvl 24 becuase I wanted to get there and see if i could get some of the rubicite for my SK.  Died about...3 seconds after zoning in, actually got a gm to answer my petition and rez me at the wiz spires there.  Then he took me safely to the zone in.  Very nice GM's back in the day, at least from my point of view.  I made the boatride/run from Tox forest or qeynos to Gfay or unrest many, many times without the use of ports,  I certainly expect the noobs of today to do the same.<br>
<br>
Morifen Wyrmtongue<br>
Rodcet Nife <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usilvius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silvius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/6/02 5:16:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=796.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbies and Ports</span><hr size=1> My first and only port came at lvl12, I had spent all my time in faydwer and hadn't been off the island much. I had traveled to far and exotic places (steamfont) once, and even took the boat to far off freeport to sell some batwings. I wanted to goto qeynos because I heard of an earing quest and a ring quest I could do for some nice items. I carefully looked over maps trying to find where I should go. I thought the karanas might be too dangerous for me with the hill giants rumored to be there, so I made the choice to goto tox and take the boat from erudin ( I had always wanted to see erudin anyway) to qeynos. I found someone to take me, who refused my money. And I gated back to felwithe after I got my earrings. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unadiar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nadiar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/6/02 8:14:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=796.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.nadiar.com/pics/sigico.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbies and Ports</span><hr size=1> I couldnt afford my level 8 spells and this drove me insane.<br>
<br>
I farmed pelts in WC for a couple weeks and managed to get enough money to not only get 136 skill  in pottery, but also managed to get enough for a Sands of Ro, and made a wisdom deity. which I sold for 250pp, which I used to make more wisdom deities... <br>
<br>
I've never been far from a little pp since. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ustumpeyfyzzbang.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stumpey Fyzzbang</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/6/02 8:26:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=796.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pages.prodigy.net/cohmsford/america.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbies and Ports</span><hr size=1> My first toon was/is a Paladin.  I levelled him to about level 17, then started Stumpey.  At that time, the Paladin had never had a port.<br>
<br>
Stumpey first asked for a port at level 2.  He was born in Ak, but wanted to go to Freeport because he hated all the hills.  Someone directed him to the Gfay spires, and he politely asked for a port.  No one responded, so he hooked up with a someone running toward  BB and ran with them.  Got an escort from a nice dwarven warrior to the docks (thank God he was there, I got attacked several times).<br>
<br>
Took the boat to Freeport and grew up.<br>
<br>
Stumpey never had a port until he turned 20 and got his own gate spells.  A nice guildie allowed bought me a copy of one gate spell (to Faymart) and brought it to Kunark where I was hunting (she was coming anyway).  <br>
<br>
Boy was that a rush.<br>
<br>
I have to admit, I hate walking now.  But I really think that travelling far with no ports is a needed right of passage in this game.  Newbies can walk. <p><font face=impact>

